1. 3 ounces of pineapple juice poured into an ice cube tray and frozen. 
2. 2 ounces of liquid pineapple juice. 
3. 1 ounce of cream of coconut. 
Directions:
1. Spoon 1 ounce of cream of coconut into a measuring cup (such as a shot glass that has markings for different measures), then pour that cup into a 16-ounce pint glass.
2. Pour 2 ounces of liquid pineapple juice into the same measuring cup. 
3. Take the frozen pineapple juice cubes and place them into the glass.
4. Using the handheld blender, mix the ingredients together. 
5. Enjoy! The mixture should be frozen, yet liquid enough to drink.
